Row click behaviour

Clicking anywhere on a row (not on the actions button) expands an inline detail panel directly below that row — it slides open smoothly with a CSS transition (transition-all duration-200). Do not navigate to a separate page.

The inline detail panel shows:


Profile photo (from profiles.photo_url) or a fallback avatar with their initial
Full name, title, bio (from profiles) — if empty, show "No profile set up yet" in muted text
Their NFC items listed as small chips: [Card — /t/abc123] [Stand — /t/xyz456] — each chip has a copy icon
A "Resend invite" button (only shown if status is "Invited")


Only one row can be expanded at a time — clicking a second row collapses the first.

Empty states


No customers → centered empty state, "No customers yet", muted subtext "Customers are added when you create an NFC item"
Search returns nothing → "No customers match your search" + "Clear search" text button


Loading state

Skeleton rows with animate-pulse — 5 rows, same column structure. Table chrome renders immediately.

